To render a React component to the DOM using React 18's `createRoot` API, follow these steps:

1. Import the `createRoot` function from the `react-dom/client` package.
2. Create a root using `createRoot` and pass the DOM container element where the React component will be rendered.
3. Call the `render` method on the root and pass your React component to it.

Here's an example:

jsx
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client';

function HelloMessage({ name }) {
  return <div>Hello {name}</div>;
}

const root = createRoot(document.getElementById('container'));
root.render(<HelloMessage name="Taylor" />);


This code will render the text "Hello Taylor" into the element with the ID `container` on the page. The `createRoot` API is part of React 18's new rendering engine, which provides improved performance and features like concurrent rendering.
